    parentName: "ol"
  }, "If the transaction is valid, the execution client adds it to its local mempool (list of pending transactions) and also broadcasts it to other nodes over the execution layer gossip network. When other nodes hear about the transaction they add it to their local mempool too. Advanced users might refrain from broadcasting their transaction and insteads forward it to specialized block builders such as ", mdx("a", {
    parentName: "li",
    "href": "https://docs.flashbots.net/flashbots-auction/overview"
  }, "Flashbots Auction"), ". This allows them to organize the transactions in upcoming blocks for maximum profit (", mdx("a", {
    parentName: "li",
    "href": "/developers/docs/mev/#mev-extraction"
